a%20%26quot%3Bdownvote%26quot%3B%20button%20for%20comment%20sections.%20This%20would%20allow%20people%20to%20anonymously%20downvote%20comments%20that%20they%20deem%20less%20%26quot%3Buseful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20first%20time%20something%20like%20this%20has%20come%20up.%20For%20nearly%20as%20long%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Blike%26quot%3B%20button%20has%20existed%20(since%202009)%2C%20the%20masses%20have%20yearned%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bdislike%26quot%3B%20button.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facebook-didnt-make-dislike-button-2016-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20has%20toyed%20around%20with%20testing%20a%20feature%20like%20this%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20ultimately%20has%20never%20done%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202016%2C%20Facebook%20added%20the%20extra%20%26quot%3Breaction%26quot%3B%20emojis%20(smiling%2C%20laughing%2C%20hugging%2C%20loving).%20Geoff%20Teehan%2C%20a%20product%20design%20director%20at%20Facebook%20at%20the%20time%2C%20wrote%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fdesignatmeta%2Freactions-not-everything-in-life-is-likable-5c403de72a3f%23.96mfarspi%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMedium%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016%3A%20%26quot%3BAbout%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20Mark%20%5BZuckerberg%5D%20brought%20together%20a%20team%20of%20people%20to%20start%20thinking%20seriously%20about%20how%20to%20make%20the%20Like%20button%20more%20expressive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeehan%20explained%20why%20they%20went%20with%20additional%20reactions%20instead%20of%20just%20a%20%26quot%3Bthumbs%20down%26quot%3B%20emoji%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EWe%20first%20needed%20to%20consider%20how%20many%20different%20reactions%20we%20should%20include.%20This%20might%20seem%20like%20a%20pretty%20straightforward%20task%3A%20Just%20slap%20a%20thumbs%20down%20next%20to%20the%20Like%20button%20and%20ship%20it.%20It's%20not%20nearly%20that%20simple%20though.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPeople%20need%20a%20much%20higher%20degree%20of%20sophistication%20and%20richness%20in%20what%20choices%20we%20provide%20for%20their%20communications.%20Binary%20'like'%20and%20'dislike'%20doesn't%20properly%20reflect%20how%20we%20react%20to%20the%20vast%20array%20of%20things%20we%20encounter%20in%20our%20real%20lives.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Facebook%20also%20tested%20out%20a%20%26quot%3Bthumbs%20down%26quot%3B%20reaction%20button%20for%20Messenger.%20This%20would've%20been%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20iMessage%20reactions%20that%20launched%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202016%20and%20included%20a%20thumbs-down%20emoji.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20considered%20something%20like%20this.%20In%20February%20of%20this%20year%2C%20Instagram%20head%20Adam%20Mosseri%20posted%20about%20a%20test%20of%20downvoting%20Instagram%20comments%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.com%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20data-text-post-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.com%2F%40mosseri%2Fpost%2FDGD12NZPjwb%5C%22%20data-text-post-version%3D%5C%220%5C%22%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.threads.com%2F%40mosseri%2Fpost%2FDGD12NZPjwb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20View%20on%20Threads%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20will%20people%20understand%20what%20the%20downvote%20arrow%20actually%20means%3F%20Will%20they%20use%20it%20on%20comments%20that%20are%20extraneous%20and%20actually%20not%20%26quot%3Buseful%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20will%20they%20use%20it%20to%20try%20to%20crush%20comments%20they%20don't%20agree%20with%20or%20don't%20like%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20Meta%20about%20this%2C%20and%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20me%20that%2C%20unlike%20past%20tests%20of%20a%20dislike%20or%20thumbs-down%20button%2C%20this%20test%20will%20explicitly%20tell%20users%20that%20it's%20about%20being%20useful%20%E2%80%94a%20little%20text%20bubble%20below%20the%20button%20will%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BLet%20us%20know%20which%20comments%20aren't%20useful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20test%20is%20still%20just%20a%20test.%20It%20might%20not%20actually%20end%20up%20being%20rolled%20out.%20Personally%2C%20I%20think%20that%20less-useful%20comments%20are%20less%20of%20a%20burning%20issue%20than%20some%20of%20the%20other%20AI-slop%20stuff%20on%20Facebook.%20(Facebook%20is%20working%20on%20combating%20some%20of%20that%2C%20too.)%20But%20hey%2C%20that's%20just%20my%20questionably%20useful%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-testing-downvote-button-mark-zuckerberg-meta-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745681695000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680bdc12a466d2b74ab43884%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-testing-downvote-button-mark-zuckerberg-meta-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Facebook%20is%20testing%20a%20downvote%20button%2C%20aiming%20to%20reduce%20spammy%20comments%20and%20allowing%20users%20to%20anonymously%20flag%20less%20useful%20content.%20Will%20it%20work%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22knotopoulos%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Notopoulos)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-testing-downvote-button-mark-zuckerberg-meta-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fear%20of%20'looking%20weak'%20is%20all%20that's%20stopping%20the%20US%20and%20China%20from%20cutting%20tariffs%2C%20Bill%20Ackman%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221238%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ackman%2C%20Bill%20Ackman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F563badf89dd7cc02308bc508%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22906%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Ackman%20said%20a%20'fear%20of%20looking%20weak'%20was%20all%20that%20was%20stopping%20the%20US%20and%20China%20from%20cutting%20tariffs.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Snyder%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBill%20Ackman%20said%20a%20fear%20of%20looking%20weak%20is%20preventing%20the%20US%20and%20China%20from%20cutting%20tariffs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20billionaire%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20said%20tariffs%20should%20fall%20to%20%26quot%3Bmore%20reasonable%20levels%26quot%3B%20of%2010%25%20to%2020%25.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20also%20questioned%20the%20belief%20that%20China%20can%20%26quot%3Bwin%26quot%3B%20a%20trade%20war%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBillionaire%20hedge%20fund%20manager%20Bill%20Ackman%20has%20said%20that%20China%20and%20the%20United%20States%20should%20dramatically%20cut%20their%20tariffs%20on%20one%20another%2C%20and%20only%20the%20fear%20of%20%26quot%3Blooking%20weak%26quot%3B%20is%20stopping%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAckman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Pershing%20Square%20who%20supported%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20during%20the%20election%2C%20made%20the%20comments%20as%20imported%20Chinese%20goods%20entering%20the%20United%20States%20face%20a%20145%25%20tariff%20and%20American%20goods%20entering%20China%20face%20a%20125%25%20tariff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpresident-donald-trump-teases-exceptions-tariffs-baseline-levies-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E10%25%20baseline%20tariff%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20all%20imports%20into%20the%20United%20States%20remains%20in%20effect%2C%20while%20Trump%20has%20paused%20his%20raft%20of%20country-specific%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAckman%2C%20who%20thanked%20Trump%20for%20announcing%20a%2090-day%20pause%20on%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-backs-off-retaliatory-tariffs-90-days-china-increase-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproposed%20%26quot%3Breciprocal%26quot%3B%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20posted%20on%20X%20on%20Saturday%20that%20tariffs%20were%20%26quot%3Bvery%20damaging%20in%20the%20short%20term%20to%20companies%20that%20rely%20on%20China%20for%20a%20large%20percentage%20of%20their%20goods.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20China%20and%20the%20United%20States%20should%20reduce%20tariffs%20to%20%26quot%3Bmore%20reasonable%20levels%20%E2%80%94%20say%2010%25%20to%2020%25%20%E2%80%94%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20thing%20stopping%20the%20reduction%20in%20tariffs%20to%20a%20more%20sensible%20level%20is%20the%20fear%20on%20the%20part%20of%20both%20countries'%20leadership%20of%20looking%20weak%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20pause%2C%20however%2C%20would%20not%20be%20a%20sign%20of%20weakness%20because%20it%20requires%20both%20countries%20to%20take%20down%20their%20tariffs.%20It%20is%20just%20common%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAckman%20also%20questioned%20the%20view%20that%20China%20could%20%26quot%3Bwin%26quot%3B%20a%20trade%20war%20with%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20with%20this%20assessment%20is%20that%2C%20the%20longer%20the%20tariffs%20persist%2C%20the%20more%20rapidly%20every%20company%20that%20has%20a%20supply%20chain%20based%20in%20China%20relocates%20it%20to%20India%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Mexico%2C%20the%20U.S.%20or%20some%20other%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Ackman%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20true%20for%20US%20and%20non-US%20companies.%20As%20a%20long-term%20player%2C%20China%20m